org.greencheek.processio.service.usage
Interface DifferenceInKBPerSecondCalculator

All Known Implementing Classes:
PrimitiveBasedDifferenceInKBPerSecondCalculator
public interface DifferenceInKBPerSecondCalculator

Given two sets of data:

  • A time
  • The amount of bytes used by the process at that time period

The two sets of data vary such that one set represents the amount of data used at that time period, previous to the amount of bytes used at the time period in the future presented by the second data set

Given the sets of data the implementing class will return in kb (kilobytes), per second, the amount of io that has occurred between the two time periods

Method Detail

getDifferenceInKbPerSecond

double getDifferenceInKbPerSecond(long previousTimeStamp,
                                  long previousBytesUsed,
                                  long currentTimeStamp,
                                  long currentBytesUsed)
Returns the amount of io, in kb per second, that has occurred between the two given timestamps. The amount of io recorded at those two times is passed to the method, and the difference between them in kb per second is returned.

Parameters:
previousTimeStamp - The previous timestamp in millis
previousBytesUsed - The amount of io used by the process at that given time
currentTimeStamp - The current timestamp in millis
currentBytesUsed - The amount of io used by the process at the given recent (current) time
Returns:
The difference in kb per second
